description: dd - convert and copy a file

subcommands.name: ascii
subcommands.description: from EBCDIC to ASCII

subcommands.name: block
subcommands.description: pad newline-terminated records with spaces to cbs-size

subcommands.name: directory
subcommands.description: fail unless a directory

subcommands.name: dsync
subcommands.description: use synchronized I/O for data

subcommands.name: ebcdic
subcommands.description: from ASCII to EBCDIC

subcommands.name: excl
subcommands.description: fail if the output file already exists

subcommands.name: fdatasync
subcommands.description: physically write output file data before finishing

subcommands.name: fsync
subcommands.description: likewise, but also write metadata

subcommands.name: fullblock
subcommands.description: accumulate full blocks of input (iflag only)

subcommands.name: ibm
subcommands.description: from ASCII to alternate EBCDIC

subcommands.name: lcase
subcommands.description: change upper case to lower case

subcommands.name: noatime
subcommands.description: do not update access time

subcommands.name: nocache
subcommands.description: Request to drop cache. See also oflag=sync

subcommands.name: nocreat
subcommands.description: do not create the output file

subcommands.name: noctty
subcommands.description: do not assign controlling terminal from file

subcommands.name: noerror
subcommands.description: continue after read errors

subcommands.name: nofollow
subcommands.description: do not follow symlinks

subcommands.name: nonblock
subcommands.description: use non-blocking I/O

subcommands.name: notrunc
subcommands.description: do not truncate the output file

subcommands.name: swab
subcommands.description: swap every pair of input bytes

subcommands.name: sync
subcommands.description: pad every input block with NULs to ibs-size; when used with block or unblock, pad with spaces rather than NULs

subcommands.name: ucase
subcommands.description: change lower case to upper case

subcommands.name: unblock
subcommands.description: replace trailing spaces in cbs-size records with newline
